CatDescriptText: Zebedee Pierce, 921 Anaheim Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 30, 1957, pg. 3 with question: "Does the financial aid, given young married couples by parents, encourage or dissuade the latter's realization of marital responsibilities?" answer reads: "I think that the aid helps the young married couples to adjust."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Zebedee Pierce wearing moustache, dark hat, eyeglasses, and plaid shirt, standing in front of a marble patterned wall with another man on the left, windows with signs that read "Federated Plans Inc. 900 Months to..." and "...aler & Crawford Reed Office Guild Opticians"
